Visualforce Section Header Components Are Secure by Default

By default, only commonly used, secure HTML elements are evaluated in the <apex:sectionHeader> componentâ€™s description attribute. Uncommon HTML elements, insecure attributes, and JavaScript are removed.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience, Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs), and all versions of the Salesforce mobile app in all editions.

For more information about this change, see Updated Default Behavior of Visualforce Section Header Components.
title: Visualforce Section Header Component Security Update
